cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the problem of L2-regularization parameter estimation in a domain adaptation setting, where there are differences between the distributions generating the training data (source domain) and the test data (target domain). This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given that the paper focuses on regularization parameter estimation, which is a common technique in machine learning, we consider cs.LG to be the most likely sub-category.
